rotational inertia of an object : how difficult it is to change velocity of the object. that includes the body&#39;s mass, but also how far each bit of mass is away from the axis. The farther out the object&#39;s mass is, the more force is required to change the rotation rate - the more rotational inertia the object has.
in the vid - the mass of the hoops is the same, but the weights of the right one are farther away - so it requires more effort to change the speed- more rotational inertia
